@component watchdog
@intent Always-on liveness watchdog (deps-0) for the live board. Guards the WS **server** and the **main bridge**, auto-restarting either if it dies — the infrastructure guarantee behind "always connected": if this stays detached-resident, the board survives individual session ends. Watches by holding a `board`-role WS connection (connect succeeds = server alive); on WS drop/connect-fail it re-checks TCP, restarts server.cjs if down, and reconnects with backoff; when the pushed AgentList lacks the main agent it restarts the bridge. A 15s backup timer revives the server if WS stays disconnected. Non-interrupt principle: never touches a live server/bridge — only spawns a replacement when one is dead, with a per-target SPAWN_COOLDOWN to avoid duplicate spawns during startup. Restarts are detached (survive the watchdog's own death). Pure runtime, no DOM. (Distilled from dashboard/live/ws-watchdog.cjs — Constellation residency layer.)
@expansion temperature=0.2 model=agent/claude template=estreux/v0.0.1
@targets vanilla
@state
wsConnected     : boolean = false   # board-role WS to server is up (= server alive)
backoff         : number = 1000     # reconnect backoff ms (cap 8000)
lastServerSpawn : number = 0        # last server restart ts (SPAWN_COOLDOWN gate)
lastBridgeSpawn : number = 0        # last bridge restart ts (SPAWN_COOLDOWN gate)
@ports
in   host       : string            # 127.0.0.1
in   port       : number            # 7878
in   serverPath : string            # server.cjs path
in   bridgePath : string            # examples/ws-local-bridge.cjs path
in   mainId     : string            # main agentId to expect in AgentList (WS_PRIMARY_AGENT; default main-agent)
out  restartServer() : detached-spawn server.cjs when server is down (cooldown-gated)
out  restartBridge() : detached-spawn the main bridge when AgentList lacks mainId (cooldown-gated)
deps ws         : websocket         # board-role connection used as a liveness probe
deps tcp        : net connect       # TCP reachability re-check before restarting server
deps spawn      : detached spawner  # spawn(node, file, {detached, stdio→log}).unref()
deps fs         : log appender      # ws-watchdog.log
@behavior
connectWs        : construct WS as board role inside try/catch — synchronous construct failure → scheduleReconnect, return. onopen → wsConnected=true, backoff=1000, log "server alive". onerror → no-op (onclose owns recovery). onclose → wsConnected=false, ws=null, scheduleReconnect.
onAgentList(m)   : on pushed AgentList — if no agent with agentId==mainId → restartBridge(); else log ok. (server pushes AgentList on connect/disconnect change; no active polling needed.)
checkServerAlive : TCP connect host:port (2s timeout) → boolean.
restartServer    : if now-lastServerSpawn < SPAWN_COOLDOWN(8000) skip; else lastServerSpawn=now, detached-spawn serverPath.
restartBridge    : if now-lastBridgeSpawn < SPAWN_COOLDOWN(8000) skip; else lastBridgeSpawn=now, detached-spawn bridgePath.
scheduleReconnect: once-pending timer (backoff) → checkServerAlive; if dead restartServer; then ALWAYS connectWs (unconditional). backoff ×2 each schedule (cap 8000); reset to 1000 on onopen.
backupTimer      : every 15s — if !wsConnected, checkServerAlive; if dead restartServer (covers missed event path).
gracefulExit(sig): SIGINT/SIGTERM → log, ws.close, process.exit(0).
@machine
# reducer: (guardState, event) → guardState
states: WATCHING(initial, WS connected) · RECONNECTING (WS down)
dispatch by event:
  WS_OPEN       : RECONNECTING → WATCHING     (entry: backoff=1000, watch AgentList)
  WS_CLOSE      : WATCHING → RECONNECTING     (entry: wsConnected=false, ws=null, scheduleReconnect)
  WS_CONSTRUCT_FAIL : * → RECONNECTING        (entry: scheduleReconnect — synchronous WS construct threw)
  agentlist_no_main : WATCHING → WATCHING     (entry: restartBridge, cooldown-gated)
  reconnect_tick : RECONNECTING → RECONNECTING (entry: if TCP dead restartServer[cooldown-gated], then ALWAYS connectWs; backoff ×2 cap 8000)
derive:
  no_interrupt ← only spawn a replacement when target is confirmed dead; live server/bridge untouched
  detached     ← all restarts spawn detached + unref → survive watchdog death (self-healing root)
